          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>The reality:</strong> Vintage buyers expect wear - it's part of authenticity. Hiding flaws = suspicion = returns when discovered. The study: Added detailed condition descriptions ("Excellent original condition, minor wear on left armrest, see photo 6"). Returns dropped from 19% to 3%. Transparency = trust = confident purchase = happy buyer.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>The escape:</strong> "Condition Details" section with bullet points. Be specific: "Excellent original condition," "Minor wear consistent with age," "Professional restoration in 2020," "Original finish with natural patina." Include photos of any flaws. Vintage buyers prefer authentic wear over refinished perfection. Patina = value. Show it clearly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-amber-700 mb-3">Trap #3: "Email for pricing" - 73% abandon, buy elsewhere</h3>
